---

Symphact is a capability-based actor runtime for secure .NET computing,
designed for co-development with the Cognitive Fabric Processing Unit (CFPU).
The CFPU's open-source reference implementation is the CLI-CPU project
(https://github.com/FenySoft/CLI-CPU).

Related work and inspiration:
  - Erlang/OTP (Ericsson) — supervision trees, let-it-crash, hot code loading
  - seL4 (UNSW / NICTA) — capability-based microkernel, formal verification
  - Singularity (Microsoft Research) — C#-based OS, Software Isolated Processes
  - QNX — deterministic message-passing microkernel
  - Akka.NET — actor framework on .NET
